Package pbxuniverse

Enum ChannelType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<ChannelType>
pbxuniverse.ChannelType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<ChannelType>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum ChannelType
extends Enum<ChannelType>
Channel types which can be used with addChannel to create LED channels. These types reflect the underlying protocol rather than the physical LED model. At this writing, most addressable LEDs use either the WS2812 (3-wire, no clock) or the APA102 (4-wire, clock required) protocol.

If using any APA102-type LEDs, you must create a clock channel. If you don't specify a clock frequency, the frequency will default to 2000000 bits/sec.
